  childSummary:"When you buy something on Amazon or Flipkart, a lot of amazing things happen behind the scenes! First, a super-smart search engine finds the product you want from 200 MILLION items in milliseconds. Then when you order, a computer picks the best warehouse to send it from — maybe one right in your city! In the warehouse, robots bring the shelves TO the workers (instead of workers walking to shelves), the item is picked, packed with protection, and labeled with a tracking code. Then it rides trucks and sometimes airplanes through sorting centers where machines read the label and send it to your city. Finally, a delivery person brings it to your door — and you can watch its journey the whole time on your phone! All of this happens in just 1-2 days for millions of orders every single day!",
